THE GAME
--------

  'Quaxim' is a Workbench game where you have to place various
horizontal, vertical and diagonal bars so they make a symmetrical
pattern on a square shaped game board.

  At the start of a game, a number of 'fixed' bars are randomly
placed. These bars cannot move, but you can click on them anytime,
so that other bars -which are moveable- will randomly appear or
disappear. When you click on a moveable bar, it will disappear and
move somewhere else... or return at the location you clicked on...

  A 'symmetry percentage' is shown at the right, it indicates the
percentage of bars that are symmetrically placed.

  Have fun!

